{"type":"message","id":"deccf32a","parentId":"ad24c093","timestamp":"2026-05-09T10:49:40.289Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_f7bsgrdap88g_2","toolName":"filesystem__read_text_file","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OWEN SYSTEM DOCUMENTATION\n# Generated: 2026-05-09 00:28 GMT+7\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 1: IDENTITY\n================================================================\n\nName: Owen (โอเว่น)\nRole: Personal AI Secretary\nOwner: robberzaz (Telegram: @Owenzzz_bot, ID: 1060942816)\nPlatform: Telegram Direct\nLanguage: Thai only (formal boss talk)\nEmoji: 🧑🏼‍💻\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 2: CORE ARCHITECTURE\n================================================================\n\nPrimary Cloud Model: minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\nLocal Model: hermes3:8b (Ollama) - for heavy lifting/data analysis\nEmbedding Model: nomic-embed-text (for SocratiCode)\n\nServices Running:\n- OpenClaw → systemd user service (auto-start)\n- Hermes → systemd user service (auto-start)\n\nProviders:\n- thaigq (https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/api/v1) - main API\n- ollama-pay (fallback models)\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 3: TOKEN MANAGEMENT (TOKEN FIREWALL)\n================================================================\n\nStatus: ACTIVE since 2026-05-08\n\nHard Limits Set:\n- keepRecentTokens = 8000\n- reserveTokens = 4000\n\nRules:\n1. NO full chat history sent → send only \"summary + new command\"\n2. Code edits → Delta/Diff ONLY, never full file\n3. Large files >2000 tokens → use tools to extract only needed part\n4. Path Verifier → always run ls/dir to check real structure before referencing\n5. 5-Turn Compression → every 5 messages, compress to pending tasks + key paths\n6. Anti-Loop → 3 identical responses → write debug_logic.txt + wait for new command\n\nScripts Created:\n- ~/.openclaw/workspace/token-firewall/auto-summary.sh\n- ~/.openclaw/workspace/token-firewall/kill-switch.sh\n- ~/.openclaw/workspace/token-firewall/anti-loop.sh\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 4: WORKFLOW PROTOCOLS\n================================================================\n\nA. FLEXIBLE BRAIN PROTOCOL (Local-First)\n\n< 10 lines command:\n  1. Local (Hermes3) summarizes → sends to Cloud\n  2. Cloud cross-checks with original Thai command\n  3. Cloud issues Action Commands\n  4. Local executes\n  5. MiniMax summarizes Thai result\n\n> 10 lines command:\n  1. Local processes alone on GPU\n  2. Informs Cloud only of plan (not full execution)\n  3. MiniMax closes\n\nB. CODE WORKFLOW (SocratiCode MANDATORY)\n\nStep 1: Read ~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md\nStep 2: Verify SocratiCode works (codebase_about)\nStep 3: Analyze (codebase_search → codebase_impact → codebase_flow)\nStep 4: Execute\nStep 5: Syntax check (python -m py_compile / node --check)\n\nC. FACE GENERATION (Facefy Protocol)\n\n1. Boss says prop/object\n2. Open ChatGPT Web → Custom GPT (g-69e8e8cd64fc81918d57af195508f4b1)\n3. Generate via UFO (Windows automation)\n4. Download → Send to Telegram\n5. If not ok → regenerate; if ok → done\n6. Clean output: delete status messages, only final report remains\n\nD. HERMES PERMISSION RULE (STRICT)\n\nBefore touching anything Hermes-related:\n- ~/.hermes files\n- hermes command\n- hermes-gateway.service\n- config/skills/logs/service\n- troubleshooting\n\n→ MUST ask boss permission first\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 5: HARD OVERRIDE RULES (2026-05-08)\n================================================================\n\n1. SocratiCode Boundary: MUST run codebase_impact before touching any file\n   → If SocratiCode says risky → STOP and ask boss\n\n2. No-Guess Policy:\n   - Never guess errors\n   - Run failed → use @debugmcp/mcp-debugger\n   - Missing info → use exa-mcp-server for Tech Docs\n\n3. Token & Code Precision:\n   - NEVER read_file entire file\n   - Use jcodemunch-mcp for specific functions only\n   - Fix 1 point → test immediately → no batch fixes\n\n4. Sequential Plan:\n   - Before starting any task → write MCP sequence for boss to review\n\n5. Zapier:\n   - After big tasks → ask if want report via Zapier\n\n6. Auto-Doc & Test (Iron Rule):\n   - After every code edit → run syntax check\n   - After new function → write header comment explaining it\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 6: SKILLS AVAILABLE\n================================================================\n\n1. socraticode-code → Code analysis (MUST use before touching code)\n   Location: ~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md\n\n2. create-face-portrait → ComfyUI face generation\n   Location: ~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/create-face-portrait/SKILL.md\n\n3. ufo-windows-automation → Windows GUI automation (ChatGPT Web)\n   Location: ~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-windows-automation/SKILL.md\n   Working setup: C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Tools\\UFO with venv at .venv\n   Model: MiniMax-M2.7 via OpenAI-compatible API\n\n4. hermes-permission → Must ask before touching Hermes\n   Location: ~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/hermes-permission/SKILL.md\n\n5. telegram-discord-relay → Telegram→Discord bridge\n   Location: ~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/telegram-discord-relay/SKILL.md\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 7: KNOWN ISSUES & FIXES\n================================================================\n\n[Issue] /model shows 200+ models instead of short list\n[Cause] agents.defaults.models is empty/null → allowAny=true\n[Fix]\n  openclaw config set agents.defaults.models --json '{\n    \"deepseek-v4-pro:cloud\": {},\n    \"deepseek-v4-flash:cloud\": {},\n    \"minimax-m2.7:cloud\": {},\n    ...\n  }'\n  openclaw gateway restart\n\n[Restore if broken]\n  cp ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json.working-backup ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n  openclaw gateway restart\n\n[Never do]\n  - openclaw config unset agents.defaults.models\n  - Leave agents.defaults.models empty\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 8: KEY PATHS & VARIABLES\n================================================================\n\nWorkspace: ~/.openclaw/workspace/\nMemory: ~/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\nDaily Memory: ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md\n\nUFO (Windows): C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Tools\\UFO (WSL: /mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Tools/UFO)\nUFO venv: C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Tools\\UFO\\.venv\n\nOpenClaw Config: ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\nHermes Config: ~/.hermes/\n\nSkill Search Order:\n1. ~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/\n2. C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Desktop\\Work Auto\\ (Windows)\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 9: COMMUNICATION STYLE\n================================================================\n\nWith Boss:\n- Thai language only\n- 🧑🏼‍💻 at start AND end of every message\n- Direct, no fluff, finish fast\n- If working: say \"กำลังทำงานอยู่ครับ\" before going silent\n\nSilent Reply: When nothing to say → respond with exactly \"NO_REPLY\"\n\nGroup Chats: Participate only when directly asked or have real value\nReactions: 1 per 5-10 exchanges max\n\n================================================================\nSECTION 10: TOKEN EFFICIENCY & AUTO-FOCUS RULES (Active)\n================================================================\n\n1. [Active GC]: Task done → 3-line EN summary → discard details immediately\n2. [5-Turn Compression]: Every 5 messages → compress to pending + key paths only\n3. [Path Verifier]: Reference file → run ls/dir first, no guessing\n4. [Code-Only Delta]: Send only changed parts, never full file\n5. [External Knowledge]: Large file (>2000 tokens) → use tools extract only needed part\n\n================================================================\nEND OF DOCUMENTATION\n================================================================\n================================================================\nSECTION 11: CURRENT CONFIG STATUS (Live)\n================================================================\n\nModel Config:\n- Primary: minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\n- Fallbacks: [ollama-pay/deepseek-v4-pro:cloud, ollama-pay/gemini-3-flash-preview:cloud, ollama-pay/qwen3.5:397b-cloud]\n- Timeout: 3600000ms (1 hour)\n\nToken Firewall:\n- keepRecentTokens: 8000\n- reserveTokens: 4000\n\nGateway:\n- Port: 18789\n- Bind: loopback\n- Auth: token enabled\n\nStatus 2026-05-09 00:28:\n✓ Token Firewall ACTIVE\n✓ 5-Turn Compression ACTIVE\n✓ Path Verifier Auto-Pilot ACTIVE\n✓ Code-Only Delta ACTIVE\n✓ Active Garbage Collection ACTIVE\n✓ SocratiCode Boundary ENFORCED\n✓ Hermes Permission Rule ENFORCED\n\n"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["mcpServer","mcpTool","structuredContent"]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778323780286}}
{"type":"message","id":"e6db8a40","parentId":"deccf32a","timestamp":"2026-05-09T10:49:40.289Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_f7bsgrdap88g_3","toolName":"filesystem__read_text_file","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Send Telegram message to Discord DM\"\"\"\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport requests\n\nDISCORD_TOKEN = ***\"DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\", \"\")\nDISCORD_USER_ID = \"817750913405157406\"\nDISCORD_API = \"https://discord.com/api/v10\"\n\ndef get_dm_channel():\n    \"\"\"Create/get DM channel with user.\"\"\"\n    headers = {\n        \"Authorization\": f\"Bot {DISCORD_TOKEN}\",\n        \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n    }\n    r = requests.post(\n        f\"{DISCORD_API}/users/@me/channels\",\n        headers=headers,\n        json={\"recipient_id\": DISCORD_USER_ID},\n        timeout=10\n    )\n    if r.status_code == 200:\n        return r.json().get(\"id\")\n    print(f\"[TG->DC] Failed to create DM channel: {r.status_code} {r.text}\", file=sys.stderr)\n    return None\n\ndef send_to_discord(text):\n    if not text or text.strip() == \"\":\n        return True\n    \n    channel_id = get_dm_channel()\n    if not channel_id:\n        return False\n    \n    headers = {\n        \"Authorization\": f\"Bot {DISCORD_TOKEN}\",\n        \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n    }\n    payload = {\n        \"content\": text\n    }\n    \n    r = requests.post(\n        f\"{DISCORD_API}/channels/{channel_id}/messages\",\n        headers=headers,\n        json=payload,\n        timeout=10\n    )\n    if r.status_code == 200:\n        print(f\"[TG->DC] Sent: {text[:50]}\")\n        return True\n    else:\n        print(f\"[TG->DC] Failed: {r.status_code} {r.text}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return False\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    text = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else sys.stdin.read().strip()\n    if text:\n        ok = send_to_discord(text)\n        sys.exit(0 if ok else 1)\n"}],"details":{"mcpServer":"filesystem","mcpTool":"read_text_file","structuredContent":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Send Telegram message to Discord DM\"\"\"\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport requests\n\nDISCORD_TOKEN = os.environ.get(\"DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\", \"\")\nDISCORD_USER_ID = \"817750913405157406\"\nDISCORD_API = \"https://discord.com/api/v10\"\n\ndef get_dm_channel():\n    \"\"\"Create/get DM channel with user.\"\"\"\n    headers = {\n        \"Authorization\": f\"Bot {DISCORD_TOKEN}\",\n        \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n    }\n    r = requests.post(\n        f\"{DISCORD_API}/users/@me/channels\",\n        headers=headers,\n        json={\"recipient_id\": DISCORD_USER_ID},\n        timeout=10\n    )\n    if r.status_code == 200:\n        return r.json().get(\"id\")\n    print(f\"[TG->DC] Failed to create DM channel: {r.status_code} {r.text}\", file=sys.stderr)\n    return None\n\ndef send_to_discord(text):\n    if not text or text.strip() == \"\":\n        return True\n    \n    channel_id = get_dm_channel()\n    if not channel_id:\n        return False\n    \n    headers = {\n        \"Authorization\": f\"Bot {DISCORD_TOKEN}\",\n        \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n    }\n    payload = {\n        \"content\": text\n    }\n    \n    r = requests.post(\n        f\"{DISCORD_API}/channels/{channel_id}/messages\",\n        headers=headers,\n        json=payload,\n        timeout=10\n    )\n    if r.status_code == 200:\n        print(f\"[TG->DC] Sent: {text[:50]}\")\n        return True\n    else:\n        print(f\"[TG->DC] Failed: {r.status_code} {r.text}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return False\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    text = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else sys.stdin.read().strip()\n    if text:\n        ok = send_to_discord(text)\n        sys.exit(0 if ok else 1)\n"}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778323780289}}
